wib:featureValueObservation.note:
Hijazi group usually has ǧ, but in some words it has y: masyid "mosque",
                  ʕāyiz "unable";
                  Ruguba, Mišaʕila, Banu ʕAmr, Sihliyya of Banu ʕAwf of Hijazi group have also gy.
                  Gy is also frequently found in Northern Central group;
                  Sheep rearers of Hijaz have dy ex: dyimal "camel", dyibāl "mountain";
                  Ḥawāzim of Banu Sālim have ǧ=k in the word ʔaṣnak "deaf";
                  fishermen of Banu Ṣubḥ + Zubaid branch in Ar-Rayis harbour have ǧ=g in migdāf "oar";
                  Northern Central group camel and sheep rearing nomads in the Ṣunaidera,
                  ʕArǧa, ʕOṯaima, Ṯādig have ǧ=dy ex: wādyid "much"
